"AWSTemplateFormatVersion: \"2010-09-09\"\nDescription: >\n  Arc 9 C8.3 - scoped IAM policy for luciel-sandbox-agent. Replaces\n  AdministratorAccess with named-action scope for CFN/CW/Logs/SSM/SNS/\n  ECS/RDS/ECR/S3-widget-cdn/CloudFront, plus explicit denies for\n  self-escalation and AdministratorAccess reattachment. Doctrine D8.1.\n  Region ca-central-1, account 729005488042.\n\nParameters:\n  AgentUserName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-sandbox-agent\n    Description: IAM user this policy is attached to.\n\n  AwsAccountId:\n    Type: String\n    Default: \"729005488042\"\n    Description: AWS account ID used for ARN composition.\n\n  AwsRegion:\n    Type: String\n    Default: ca-central-1\n    Description: Region used for ARN composition.\n\nResources:\n  LucielSandboxAgentPolicy:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::ManagedPolicy\n    Properties:\n      ManagedPolicyName: luciel-sandbox-agent-scoped\n      Description: \"Arc 9 C8.3 scoped permissions for luciel-sandbox-agent. Replaces AdministratorAccess. Doctrine D8.1.\"\n      Users:\n        - !Ref AgentUserName\n      PolicyDocument:\n        Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n        Statement:\n          # ---- Read-only basics (whole account) -------------------\n          # Caller-identity is required by virtually every CLI session\n          # for sanity checks and is harmless.\n          - Sid: AllowSelfIdentity\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - sts:GetCallerIdentity\n              - iam:GetUser\n              - iam:ListAttachedUserPolicies\n              - iam:ListUserPolicies\n              - iam:GetPolicy\n              - iam:GetPolicyVersion\n              - iam:GetUserPolicy\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:iam::${AwsAccountId}:user/${AgentUserName}\"\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:iam::${AwsAccountId}:policy/luciel-sandbox-agent-scoped\"\n\n          # ---- CloudFormation: manage luciel-prod-* stacks --------\n          # describe-stacks/list-stacks need * because CFN does not\n          # support resource-arn on list operations.\n          - Sid: AllowCfnList\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - cloudformation:List*\n              - cloudformation:Describe*\n              - cloudformation:Get*\n              - cloudformation:ValidateTemplate\n            Resource: \"*\"\n\n          - Sid: AllowCfnWriteOnLucielProd\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - cloudformation:CreateStack\n              - cloudformation:UpdateStack\n              - cloudformation:DeleteStack\n              - cloudformation:CreateChangeSet\n              - cloudformation:DescribeChangeSet\n              - cloudformation:ExecuteChangeSet\n              - cloudformation:DeleteChangeSet\n              - cloudformation:ListChangeSets\n              - cloudformation:CancelUpdateStack\n              - cloudformation:ContinueUpdateRollback\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:cloudformation:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:stack/luciel-*/*\"\n\n          # ---- IAM resources the CFN templates create -------------\n          # luciel-sandbox-agent-policy template provisions a managed\n          # policy and attaches it to the user. luciel-prod-verify-role\n          # creates a task role. We allow create/update/delete on these\n          # specific names so the templates remain operable, but DENY\n          # any iam:* on the agent's own privileges below.\n          - Sid: AllowIamForCfnManagedResources\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - iam:CreatePolicy\n              - iam:DeletePolicy\n              - iam:CreatePolicyVersion\n              - iam:DeletePolicyVersion\n              - iam:ListPolicyVersions\n              - iam:AttachUserPolicy\n              - iam:DetachUserPolicy\n              - iam:ListEntitiesForPolicy\n              - iam:CreateRole\n              - iam:DeleteRole\n              - iam:GetRole\n              - iam:UpdateAssumeRolePolicy\n              - iam:PutRolePolicy\n              - iam:DeleteRolePolicy\n              - iam:AttachRolePolicy\n              - iam:DetachRolePolicy\n              - iam:PassRole\n              - iam:TagRole\n              - iam:UntagRole\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:iam::${AwsAccountId}:policy/luciel-sandbox-agent-scoped\"\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:iam::${AwsAccountId}:role/luciel-*\"\n\n          # ---- CloudWatch alarms + metric filters -----------------\n          - Sid: AllowCloudWatchReads\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - cloudwatch:DescribeAlarms\n              - cloudwatch:DescribeAlarmHistory\n              - cloudwatch:DescribeAlarmsForMetric\n              - cloudwatch:ListMetrics\n              - cloudwatch:GetMetricStatistics\n              - cloudwatch:GetMetricData\n            Resource: \"*\"\n\n          - Sid: AllowCloudWatchAlarmWrites\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - cloudwatch:PutMetricAlarm\n              - cloudwatch:DeleteAlarms\n              - cloudwatch:SetAlarmState\n              - cloudwatch:EnableAlarmActions\n              - cloudwatch:DisableAlarmActions\n              - cloudwatch:TagResource\n              - cloudwatch:UntagResource\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:cloudwatch:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:alarm:luciel-*\"\n\n          # ---- CloudWatch Logs ------------------------------------\n          # Synthetic log injection in C7 validation uses\n          # PutLogEvents on /ecs/luciel-backend. Filter creation +\n          # describe needed for stack updates.\n          - Sid: AllowLogsList\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - logs:Describe*\n              - logs:Get*\n              - logs:FilterLogEvents\n              - logs:StartQuery\n              - logs:StopQuery\n            Resource: \"*\"\n\n          - Sid: AllowLogsWriteOnLucielGroups\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - logs:CreateLogGroup\n              - logs:DeleteLogGroup\n              - logs:CreateLogStream\n              - logs:DeleteLogStream\n              - logs:PutLogEvents\n              - logs:PutMetricFilter\n              - logs:DeleteMetricFilter\n              - logs:PutRetentionPolicy\n              - logs:TagLogGroup\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:logs:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:log-group:/ecs/luciel-*\"\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:logs:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:log-group:/ecs/luciel-*:*\"\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:logs:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:log-group:/aws/lambda/luciel-*\"\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:logs:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:log-group:/aws/lambda/luciel-*:*\"\n\n          # ---- SSM Parameter Store --------------------------------\n          # PagerDuty rotation needs Put on /luciel/prod/pagerduty/*.\n          # Other /luciel/* params are read-only (creds: rotated by\n          # the operator out-of-band, not by the agent).\n          - Sid: AllowSsmReadOnLucielParams\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - ssm:GetParameter\n              - ssm:GetParameters\n              - ssm:GetParameterHistory\n              - ssm:DescribeParameters\n              - ssm:ListTagsForResource\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:ssm:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:parameter/luciel/*\"\n\n          - Sid: AllowSsmWriteOnPagerDutyParams\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - ssm:PutParameter\n              - ssm:DeleteParameter\n              - ssm:DeleteParameters\n              - ssm:AddTagsToResource\n              - ssm:RemoveTagsFromResource\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:ssm:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:parameter/luciel/prod/pagerduty/*\"\n\n          # ---- SNS -----------------------------------------------\n          - Sid: AllowSnsReads\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - sns:List*\n              - sns:Get*\n            Resource: \"*\"\n\n          - Sid: AllowSnsWriteOnLucielProd\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - sns:CreateTopic\n              - sns:DeleteTopic\n              - sns:Publish\n              - sns:Subscribe\n              - sns:Unsubscribe\n              - sns:ConfirmSubscription\n              - sns:SetTopicAttributes\n              - sns:SetSubscriptionAttributes\n              - sns:TagResource\n              - sns:UntagResource\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:sns:${AwsRegion}:${AwsAccountId}:luciel-prod-*\"\n\n          # ---- ECS describes (read-only on luciel-cluster) --------\n          # Needed for deploy-status checks during stack updates and\n          # for the worker autoscaling stack's targets.\n          - Sid: AllowEcsReads\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - ecs:DescribeClusters\n              - ecs:DescribeServices\n              - ecs:DescribeTasks\n              - ecs:DescribeTaskDefinition\n              - ecs:ListServices\n              - ecs:ListTasks\n              - ecs:ListClusters\n              - ecs:ListTaskDefinitions\n            Resource: \"*\"\n\n          # ---- RDS describes (read-only) --------------------------\n          # The alarms stack references the RDS instance by name and\n          # we sometimes verify storage/connection metrics manually.\n          - Sid: AllowRdsReads\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - rds:DescribeDBInstances\n              - rds:DescribeDBClusters\n              - rds:DescribeDBSnapshots\n              - rds:ListTagsForResource\n            Resource: \"*\"\n\n          # ---- ECR + ECS deploy paths (read-only for now) ---------\n          # If/when we move ECS service updates into the agent's\n          # scope, expand to luciel-* repositories specifically.\n          - Sid: AllowEcrReads\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - ecr:DescribeRepositories\n              - ecr:DescribeImages\n              - ecr:ListImages\n              - ecr:GetAuthorizationToken\n              - ecr:BatchGetImage\n              - ecr:GetDownloadUrlForLayer\n            Resource: \"*\"\n\n          # ---- S3: widget-cdn bucket only -------------------------\n          - Sid: AllowS3WidgetCdn\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - s3:ListBucket\n              - s3:GetObject\n              - s3:PutObject\n              - s3:DeleteObject\n              - s3:GetBucketLocation\n              - s3:GetBucketPolicy\n            Resource:\n              - \"arn:aws:s3:::luciel-widget-cdn*\"\n              - \"arn:aws:s3:::luciel-widget-cdn*/*\"\n\n          # ---- CloudFront read (widget CDN) -----------------------\n          - Sid: AllowCloudFrontReads\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - cloudfront:ListDistributions\n              - cloudfront:GetDistribution\n              - cloudfront:GetDistributionConfig\n              - cloudfront:CreateInvalidation\n              - cloudfront:GetInvalidation\n              - cloudfront:ListInvalidations\n            Resource: \"*\"\n\n          # ---- One-shot self-detach of AdministratorAccess -------\n          # Required by the C8.3 zero-downtime overlap pattern: after\n          # the scoped policy is attached and smoke-tested alongside\n          # Admin, the agent detaches Admin from itself. Detachment\n          # only de-privileges -- re-attachment is blocked by\n          # DenyAdminPolicyAttachment below. Scoped to the Admin\n          # policy ARN only.\n          - Sid: AllowSelfDetachAdmin\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - iam:DetachUserPolicy\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:iam::${AwsAccountId}:user/${AgentUserName}\"\n            Condition:\n              ArnEquals:\n                iam:PolicyARN: \"arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AdministratorAccess\"\n\n          # ---- Explicit denies (defence in depth) -----------------\n          # The agent must NEVER be able to modify its own privileges\n          # or create a new IAM user / access key for itself.\n          # This explicit deny survives even if a future allow stanza\n          # gets too broad on iam:*.\n          - Sid: DenySelfPrivilegeEscalation\n            Effect: Deny\n            Action:\n              - iam:CreateUser\n              - iam:DeleteUser\n              - iam:CreateAccessKey\n              - iam:DeleteAccessKey\n              - iam:UpdateAccessKey\n              - iam:CreateLoginProfile\n              - iam:DeleteLoginProfile\n              - iam:UpdateLoginProfile\n              - iam:PutUserPolicy\n              - iam:DeleteUserPolicy\n              # iam:DetachUserPolicy intentionally NOT denied here --\n              # detaching only DE-privileges and never escalates.\n              # Allowing self-detach lets the agent clean up\n              # AdministratorAccess after the C8.3 zero-downtime\n              # overlap. Reattachment of Admin remains blocked by\n              # DenyAdminPolicyAttachment below.\n              - iam:AttachUserPolicy\n              - iam:AddUserToGroup\n              - iam:RemoveUserFromGroup\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:iam::${AwsAccountId}:user/${AgentUserName}\"\n\n          # Block any attempt to touch the AdministratorAccess managed\n          # policy itself (extra belt + braces).\n          - Sid: DenyAdminPolicyAttachment\n            Effect: Deny\n            Action:\n              - iam:AttachUserPolicy\n              - iam:AttachRolePolicy\n              - iam:AttachGroupPolicy\n            Resource: \"*\"\n            Condition:\n              ArnEquals:\n                iam:PolicyARN: \"arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AdministratorAccess\"\n\nOutputs:\n  PolicyArn:\n    Value: !Ref LucielSandboxAgentPolicy\n    Description: ARN of the scoped policy now attached to the user.\n\n  AttachedTo:\n    Value: !Ref AgentUserName\n    Description: IAM user the policy is attached to.\n"
